nodes.text: Jodie Marie Comer (born March 11, 1993) is a British actress who portrays Rey's mother in the 2019 film Star Wars: Episode IX The Rise of Skywalker. She is best known for playing Russian assassin Oksana Astankova / Villanelle in the spy thriller series Killing Eve, for which she won a BAFTA Award for Best Actress and an Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series. Other roles of note include Chloe Gemell in the comedy-drama series My Mad Fat Diary, Ivy Moxam in the 2016 drama miniseries Thirteen, and Elizabeth of York in the 2017 historical miniseries The White Princess.
